&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Electric Hydrogen&lt;/strong&gt;’s mission is to make molecules to decarbonize our world! Our outstanding people are our most important asset and will allow us to deliver hydrogen from renewable electrolysis for heavy industry, at prices below fossil fuels.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;We are seeking a Quality Manager to develop our plant quality programs and lead quality execution for our European electrolysis plant projects. In this role, you will be responsible for building and managing quality systems, processes, and personnel that support successful project delivery from product development through fabrication, construction, commissioning, and customer handover. You will partner closely with Engineering, Supply Chain, Manufacturing, and Project Delivery teams to ensure the highest standards of quality, compliance, and customer satisfaction across our European projects.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is based in Europe and reports to the VP, Product Engineering.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Primary Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul data-spread=&quot;false&quot;&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;line-height: 2;&quot;&gt;Lead quality activities throughout the full lifecycle of product development, procurement, fabrication, construction, and project delivery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;line-height: 2;&quot;&gt;Develop and manage quality processes, procedures, and programs to support successful project execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;line-height: 2;&quot;&gt;Build, contract, and manage quality personnel and third-party inspection resources to support procurement, fabrication, and construction activities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;line-height: 2;&quot;&gt;Develop Inspection and Test Plans (ITPs) and establish quality hold points throughout fabrication, manufacturing, and construction processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;line-height: 2;&quot;&gt;Provide quality leadership and oversight during project construction activities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;line-height: 2;&quot;&gt;Deliver quality updates and project quality reporting to internal stakeholders and customers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;line-height: 2;&quot;&gt;Own the non-conformance management process, including root cause analysis and corrective action implementation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;line-height: 2;&quot;&gt;Partner with Supply Chain to build, maintain, and continuously improve the Approved Vendor List (AVL)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;line-height: 2;&quot;&gt;Evaluate suppliers for ISO 9001, ISO 3834-2, and other applicable certifications required for hydrogen and oxygen service equipment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;line-height: 2;&quot;&gt;Review and approve fabricator drawings, weld maps, material lists, and manufacturing documentation for compliance with project specifications, codes, and customer requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;line-height: 2;&quot;&gt;Develop project-specific quality requirements and quality clauses for inclusion in supplier contracts and purchase orders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;line-height: 2;&quot;&gt;Coordinate PED 2014/68/EU conformity assessments with notified bodies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;line-height: 2;&quot;&gt;Own project EU Technical Files and issue EU Declarations of Conformity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;line-height: 2;&quot;&gt;Develop and approve FAT and SAT procedures and lead Factory Acceptance Testing activities at supplier facilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;line-height: 2;&quot;&gt;Resolve punch-list items and quality issues prior to shipment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;line-height: 2;&quot;&gt;Review and approve packaging, preservation, and transportation documentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;line-height: 2;&quot;&gt;Own End-of-Manufacturing Record Books and ensure compliance with PED and project requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
